A

addPlayer(UUID) - Method in class com.deadmandungeons.audioconnect.PlayerScheduler
Add a player to this scheduler to begin scheduled execution of PlayerScheduler.PlayerDataWriter.writeData(Player) for the player.
If a player identified by the given ID is not online during scheduled execution, the playerId will be removed from this scheduler.

PlayerScheduler - Class in com.deadmandungeons.audioconnect
This class facilitates the scheduled execution of a repeated data processing task for a set of players in an efficient manner through load balancing.
Players added to this scheduler are partitioned into separate tasks which are executed at different times (or ticks) displaced from each other as a means to balance the load.
PlayerScheduler(Plugin, PlayerScheduler.PlayerDataWriter, int) - Constructor for class com.deadmandungeons.audioconnect.PlayerScheduler
Construct a new PlayerScheduler Note: maximumTasks will be set as the given tickFrequency, so this is equivalent to: PlayerScheduler(plugin, writer, tickFrequency, tickFrequency)
PlayerScheduler(Plugin, PlayerScheduler.PlayerDataWriter, int, int) - Constructor for class com.deadmandungeons.audioconnect.PlayerScheduler
Construct a new PlayerScheduler
PlayerScheduler.PlayerDataWriter - Interface in com.deadmandungeons.audioconnect
The interface defining basic player data processing methods to be executed by a PlayerScheduler
